# Spotify Web API client ID for the now-playing / listening-history pairing.
#
# EchoVault uses the Authorization Code + PKCE flow, so NO client secret is
# needed and nothing is stored server-side. To enable Spotify pairing:
#
#   1. Create an app at https://developer.spotify.com/dashboard
#   2. In the app settings, add a Redirect URI that exactly matches where you
#      serve EchoVault, e.g. http://127.0.0.1:5173/ for local dev
#      (Spotify requires 127.0.0.1 rather than localhost for http redirects),
#      or your deployed https URL.
#   3. Copy the app's Client ID below, then rebuild.
#
# You can also skip this file and paste the Client ID at runtime via the
# "Set up Spotify" button — it's stored only in your browser.
VITE_SPOTIFY_CLIENT_ID=
